<DocsLayout title="buoy ahoy" description="Manage your Buoy Cloud account and integrations">
  <h1>buoy ahoy</h1>

  <p>
    Manage your Buoy Cloud account, Git integrations, and billing.
    Also available as <code>buoy ship</code>.
  </p>

  <h2>Usage</h2>

  <pre><code>buoy ahoy &lt;command&gt; [options]</code></pre>

  <h2>Commands</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Command</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>login</code></td>
        <td>Authenticate with Buoy Cloud</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>logout</code></td>
        <td>Sign out and clear credentials</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>status</code></td>
        <td>Show current authentication and account status</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>github</code></td>
        <td>Connect or manage GitHub integration</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>gitlab</code></td>
        <td>Connect or manage GitLab integration (coming soon)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>billing</code></td>
        <td>Open billing portal in your browser</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>plans</code></td>
        <td>View available plans and current usage</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Options</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Command</th>
        <th>Option</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>status</code></td>
        <td><code>--json</code></td>
        <td>Output status as JSON</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>github</code></td>
        <td><code>--json</code></td>
        <td>Output GitHub connection info as JSON</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>github</code></td>
        <td><code>--disconnect</code></td>
        <td>Disconnect GitHub integration</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Examples</h2>

  <h3>Login</h3>

  <pre><code>$ buoy ahoy login

Opening browser for authentication...

✓ Authenticated as dylan@example.com
  Plan: Founding Member
  Org: Acme Inc</code></pre>

  <h3>Check status</h3>

  <pre><code>$ buoy ahoy status

Account Status
──────────────
User: dylan@example.com
Plan: Founding Member
Org: Acme Inc
GitHub: connected (acme-org)
GitLab: not connected</code></pre>

  <h3>Connect GitHub</h3>

  <pre><code>$ buoy ahoy github

Opening browser to install Buoy GitHub App...

✓ GitHub connected
  Organization: acme-org
  Repositories: 12 accessible</code></pre>

  <h3>Disconnect GitHub</h3>

  <pre><code>$ buoy ahoy github --disconnect

Disconnect GitHub integration? (y/N) y

✓ GitHub disconnected</code></pre>

  <h3>View plans</h3>

  <pre><code>$ buoy ahoy plans

Current Plan: Founding Member
─────────────────────────────
Repos: unlimited
Scans: unlimited
PR checks: ✓
Priority support: ✓

Available Plans
───────────────
Free        $0/mo     3 repos, basic scanning
Pro         $29/mo    unlimited repos, PR checks
Enterprise  custom    SSO, dedicated support</code></pre>

  <h3>Manage billing</h3>

  <pre><code>$ buoy ahoy billing

Opening billing portal in browser...</code></pre>

  <h3>Logout</h3>

  <pre><code>$ buoy ahoy logout

✓ Signed out. Credentials cleared.</code></pre>

  <h3>JSON output</h3>

  <pre><code>$ buoy ahoy status --json

&#123;
  "user": "dylan@example.com",
  "plan": "founding-member",
  "org": "Acme Inc",
  "github": &#123;
    "connected": true,
    "org": "acme-org",
    "repos": 12
  &#125;,
  "gitlab": &#123;
    "connected": false
  &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>

  <h2>Alias</h2>

  <p>
    <code>buoy ship</code> is an alias for <code>buoy ahoy</code>. Both commands are identical.
  </p>

  <pre><code>$ buoy ship status
# same as: buoy ahoy status</code></pre>

